<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,258,607]" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,330,355]" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</emphasis>
The females of 
<taxonomicName box="[516,617,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis box="[516,539,332,355]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[558,617,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">velox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are separated from those of other 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1137,330,355]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1035,1137,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following combination of characters: antenna black; flagellum almost 1.8 times longer than pedicel; longitudinal pollinose bands on scutum inconspicuous; legs predominantly black; abdomen black; tergite 2 with a pair of vague lateral orange maculae; tergites 2–4 with a pair of widely interrupted greyish pollinose fasciae. The male genitalia were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hurkmans" box="[312,518,474,499]" pageId="18" pageNumber="45" refString="Hurkmans, W. (1993) A monograph of Merodon (Diptera: Syrphidae). Part 1. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 136, 147 - 234." type="journal article" year="1993">Hurkmans (1993)</bibRefCitation>
. This species was collected in the eastern areas of 
<collectingRegion box="[1120,1195,474,499]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Elburz</collectingRegion>
Mountains, near the border with 
<collectingCountry box="[294,452,510,535]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
. Prior to the present study, 
<taxonomicName box="[775,875,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis box="[775,875,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">M. velox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had only been collected from some parts of the 
<collectingRegion box="[151,230,546,571]" country="Turkmenistan" name="Balkan Welayaty" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Balkan</collectingRegion>
Peninsula (former 
<collectingCountry box="[451,579,546,571]" name="Serbia" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Yugoslavia</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry box="[592,674,547,571]" name="Greece" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Greece</collectingCountry>
, including Lesvos island) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1104,546,571]" name="Turkey" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ricarte" box="[1120,1337,546,571]" pageId="18" pageNumber="45" refString="Ricarte, A., Nedeljkovic, Z., Rotheray, G. E., Lyszkowski, R. M., Hancock, E. G., Watt, K., Hewitt, S. M., Horsfield, D. &amp; Wilkinson, G. (2012) Syrphidae (Diptera) from the Greek island of Lesvos, with description of two new species. Zootaxa, 3175, 1 - 23." type="journal article" year="2012">
Ricarte 
<emphasis box="[1211,1261,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="45">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
; Speight 2016).
</paragraph>
